examples: In our family of five, we have to do the laundry every other day.

definitions.definition: A place or room where laundering is done - including, by extension , other forms of laundering than clothes washing .
That which needs to be, is being, or has been laundered .
examples: You've left your dirty laundry all over the house.

definitions.definition: A business whose primary purpose is to conceal the origins of money received illegally.
